<HEAD>Israeli Peace Crusader Meets With Arafat</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Israeli peace crusader <PERSON> Abie </PERSON> <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> could be criminally prosecuted for holding talks with <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> chief <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> and offering a peace plan that calls for mutual recognition, <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> radio </ORGANIZATION> reported today. The meeting prompted a political storm in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>. Right-wing legislators said <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> should to be tried for treason, but left-wing politicians praised the meeting as an important step toward ending the 9-month-old <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> uprising in the occupied lands. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> radio said <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> recently met with <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> in <LOCATION> Tunis </LOCATION> and presented the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> leader with a peace plan that includes mutual recognition between <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, a <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> agreement to a 100-day moratorium on violence, and an end to the Palestinian uprising in the occupied <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON>'s plan also calls for the release of <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> soldiers missing or captured in <LOCATION> Lebanon </LOCATION> in exchange for the Israeli release of thousands of Palestinians detained since the uprising began Dec. 8, <ORGANIZATION> Israel </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> radio </ORGANIZATION> said. According to the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nations </ORGANIZATION>, more than 260 Palestinians have been killed in the uprising and five Israelis also have died. <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> said <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> promised to consider the peace proposals after he meets Tuesday with socialist members of the <ORGANIZATION> European </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Strasbourg </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>, according to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> radio. <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON>, who founded the <ORGANIZATION> Voice </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Peace </ORGANIZATION> radio station in 1973, could face prosecution and a prison sentence of up to three years for his visit with the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> leader. The meeting violates a 1986 Israeli law barring unauthorized contacts with members of terrorist groups. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> views the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> as a terrorist group. Four Israeli leftists are serving six-month prison terms for meeting with <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> members in <LOCATION> Romania </LOCATION> in 1986. <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> hopes to brief Prime Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> and Foreign Minister <PERSON> Shimon </PERSON> <PERSON> Peres </PERSON> on his encounter with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> chief when he returns to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> radio said. Both <PERSON> Peres </PERSON>, who favors an international <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> peace conference, and <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>, who opposes such a forum, have staunchly refused to include the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> in peace negotiations. Right-wing legislator <PERSON> Yuval </PERSON> <PERSON> Nehman </PERSON> of the <ORGANIZATION> Tehiya </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> demanded that <PERSON> Nathan </PERSON> be arrested on his return to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> for illegally meeting with an enemy, the radio said. But two <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> left-wing parties _ Mapam and the Progressive List for Peace _ praised <PERSON> Nathan </PER