 she had her vodka. I saw her fight him over a drink several times.'' Police said the couple left <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> in August 1987, criss-crossing the country in a van for several months before arriving in <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION>, where T'Souvas hoped to get a construction job. Police said <PERSON> Kathleen </PERSON>'s diary showed they lived in the van, often parking it near Three Rivers Stadium, as they fished in the rivers, sold their blood for money and worked part-time in a food kitchen for the homeless. After the van broke down they built a makeshift shelter on the banks of the <LOCATION> Monongahela </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>, according to police. On Sept. 3, police said, the couple and a homeless man, <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Bozic </PERSON>, 42, spent the day drinking, fishing and using <PERSON> Bozic </PERSON>'s .22 - caliber pistol to shoot rats and cans under While <PERSON> Bozic </PERSON> was gone to get food, police said, the couple argued over a bottle of vodka T'Souvas had. Police said the woman took <PERSON> Bozic </PERSON>'s gun and shot T'Souvas once in the head. <PERSON> Bozic </PERSON> said he did n't realize <PERSON> T'Souvas </PERSON> was dead until the next morning, when the woman said she could n't rouse him, authorities said. <PERSON> Kathleen </PERSON> <PERSON> T'Souvas </PERSON> was charged with criminal homicide and was being held without bail at the <LOCATION> Allegheny </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jail </LOCATION>. A coroner's hearing is scheduled Thursday <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> T'Souvas </PERSON> said he talked to his son a few days before his death. `` I just tried to tell him to put it together and come home,'' the father said. `` I sent him some money, but he never came.''
