 <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> ridiculed <PERSON> Michael </PERSON> <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON>' national security credentials Tuesday with jokes about the Democratic nominee's `` rubber duck'' naval adviser and foreign policy dealings limited to his <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> neighbors At a rally of several hundred supporters in <LOCATION> Bismarck </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Republican </ORGANIZATION> vice presidential candidate said <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> was `` dangerously naive'' on national security and `` the most anti-defense candidate on a national level since <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> McGovern </PERSON>.'' Earlier, <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> told backers in the <LOCATION> Milwaukee </LOCATION> suburb of <LOCATION> Wauwatosa </LOCATION> it was `` shocking'' that <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> found it necessary to receive defense briefings last weekend from members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION>. `` He does n't know enough about national defense,'' said the <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION> senator. `` He has to stop in and ask members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> that I've been working with for the past 12 years.'' On a day when <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> delivered a major speech on U.S.-Soviet relations in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION>, <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> said the <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> governor does n't have `` the understanding or qualifications'' to run for president. `` Want to hear a sad story about the <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> campaign?'' <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> asked. `` The governor of <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION>, he lost his top naval adviser last week. His rubber duck drowned in his bathtub,'' <PERSON> Quayle </PERSON> said to roars of laughter from his audience at <ORGANIZATION> Bush-Quayle </ORGANIZATION> campaign headquarters for <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> press secretary <PERSON> Dayton </