<NOTE>Eds: Adds 1 graf at end to UPDATE with highest rating yet for Fox.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 There she is, No. 1 in the weekly Nielsen ratings, <LOCATION> Miss </LOCATION> <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> estimates that between 50 and 55 million viewers watched all or part of `` The Miss American Pageant'' on Saturday night. It was the highest-ranked pageant since 1982's was No. 1. This year's pageant rated 22.3 with a 44 share, an improvement over last year's, which had a rating of 20.4 and a 42 share, according to the <ORGANIZATION> A.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nielsen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co </ORGANIZATION>. The highest-rated pageant was in 1986 when it got a 23.0 rating and a 44 share. Each rating point represents 886,000 homes with televisions. The share is a percentage of sets in use. The other two networks ran college football games against the pageant that ended up ranked 59th and 60th, respectively. The two <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> shows that preceded Miss <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> on Saturday ranked second and third in the weekly ratings. One of them was especially good news for <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>, the preview of a new show, `` Baby Boom,'' based on the movie by the same name and starring <PERSON> Kate </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> as an executive who inherits a baby. It ranked third. It had preceded Miss <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> and followed `` Golden Girls,'' which was No. 2 in the ratings. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> said the `` Baby Boom'' rating was the highest this season for the network in that time period. The rest of the top 10 were: `` The Cosby Show'' <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>, `` Monday Night Football _ <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> vs. <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Giants </ORGANIZATION>'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>, the Bob Hope Special on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>, `` Full House'' on <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGAN