. CBS and <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` World News Tonight'' tied with a rating of 9.5. `` NBC Nightly News'' had a 9.4. Each of the three got a 20 share. <ORGANIZATION> Fox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> recorded the highest rating yet for its prime-time series when `` <LOCATION> America </LOCATION>'s Most Wanted,'' with got a 9.0 and ranked 43rd among all network shows. Two other <PERSON> Fox </PERSON> shows, `` Married ... with Children'' and `` 21 Jump Street'' also landed high enough in the ratings to out-rank several network programs.
