> let chemical weapons experts go there to investigate claims that <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> used poison gas to crush the Kurdish uprising. <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> denies using gas against the Kurds, but previously acknowledged using chemical weapons against <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> in their 8-year-old war. An <LOCATION> Iraqi </LOCATION> official said in <LOCATION> Baghdad </LOCATION> that <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> probably would not admit such a proposed <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> team as a matter of sovereignty.
