<HEAD>Gulf Coast States Brace for Gilbert's Wrath</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Hurricane Gilbert Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Residents along the <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gulf </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday braced for the possible onslaught of Hurricane <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON>, which ripped through <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Cayman </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION> with winds of 140 mph before taking aim at the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION>. In <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>, oil companies evacuated thousands of workers from rigs in the gulf, and residents along the coast awaited word on whether <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> would become the second storm to hit them in a week. And on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Mercantile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, oil futures prices moved up a bit Tuesday, driven by a rise in gasoline prices spurred by concerns about the effects of the hurricane. `` Oh man, business is really booming,'' said <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Shannon </PERSON>, an assistant manager at a <ORGANIZATION> Wal-Mart </ORGANIZATION> store in <LOCATION> Galveston </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Texas </LOCATION>. `` We've got people all over the place right now buying flashlights, batteries, lamp oil _ everything `` It's very steady and they're not just coming in getting a handful of stuff _ it's cartloads of stuff.'' <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON>, which could hit the <LOCATION> Gulf </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Mexico </LOCATION> by Thursday, reached Category 5 on the Saffir-Simpson scale of hurricane strength. The scale lists such a storm as causing catastrophic damage and having a storm surge of greater than 18 feet. `` Everyone's buying plywood,'' <PERSON> Ricky </PERSON> <PERSON> Burge </PERSON>, an assistant manager at <PERSON> McCoy </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> Building </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LO