<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Officials from <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Cayman </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION> readied relief efforts Tuesday as they anxiously awaited details on the damage wrought by <PERSON> Hurricane </PERSON> <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON>'s passage through their home islands. A <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> C-130 plane with international and <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> officials aboard went to <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION> to set up a satellite communication system to coordinate help in the giant hurricane's aftermath `` This hurricane from what I can gather is about the worst in its -LRB- <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION>'s -RRB- history,'' said <PERSON> Percival </PERSON> <PERSON> R. </PERSON> <PERSON> Todd </PERSON>, <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION>'s deputy consul-general in <LOCATION> Miami </LOCATION>. `` It just souped up over the entirety of <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION>. There's no place on the island that escaped.'' <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> missed most of <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION>, bringing strong winds, rain squalls and tides 1 to 2 feet above normal to the <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Keys </LOCATION>. But officials of <LOCATION> Jamaica </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Cayman </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION>, a British colony, were preparing to hear the worst. `` We experienced Hurricane Charlie, so we're accustomed to savage attacks by tropical storms,'' <PERSON> Todd </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Charlie </PERSON> was the last major hurricane to strike the island directly, claiming 111 lives in 1951, he said. Serious flooding had already swamped the <LOCATION> Cayman </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Islands </LOCATION> by Tuesday afternoon, and officials there expected heavy damage, said <PERSON> Erina </PERSON> <PERSON> Nichols </PERSON>, a spokeswoman for the <ORGANIZATION> Cayman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATIO