<HEAD>Investigators Interview Pilot, Then He Leaves Hospital</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAVE PEGO</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Investigators from the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Transportation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Safety </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> talked with the captain of <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> Flight 1141 for the first time Tuesday afternoon, but gleaned no information that could pinpoint the cause of the Aug. 31 crash, a board member said. `` He does not know why this plane crashed,'' said <PERSON> Lee </PERSON> <PERSON> Dickinson </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON>, who summarized the <ORGANIZATION> NTSB </ORGANIZATION>'s interview with <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> Capt. <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> in a telephone interview from <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION>, <PERSON> D.C. </PERSON> <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, who spent nearly two hours talking with investigators, had been at Parkland Memorial Hospital since his <ORGANIZATION> Boeing </ORGANIZATION> 727 crashed as it took off from <LOCATION> Dallas-Fort </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION>, killing 14. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>, one of 94 survivors, was discharged from the hospital following the <ORGANIZATION> NTSB </ORGANIZATION> interview. Wearing a back brace and with his mouth wired shut, he left the hospital with his wife and <ORGANIZATION> Delta </ORGANIZATION> officials, a hospital spokeswoman said. <PERSON> Dickinson </PERSON> said the <ORGANIZATION> NTSB </ORGANIZATION> had n't expected the interview with captain to yield a clue that might solve the puzzling crash, although investigators had been awaiting permission to talk to <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON>' physician had barred investigators from interviewing <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> earlier. <PERSON> Davis </PERSON> told investigators that the flight from <LOCATION> Jackson </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Miss. </LOCATION>, to <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> had been uneventful, and that eve