the cavalry to the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corps </ORGANIZATION> in 1931. <PERSON> Norstad </PERSON> was named president of <ORGANIZATION> Owens-Corning </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Fiberglas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> after he retired from the military. He is survived by his wife, <PERSON> Isabelle </PERSON> <PERSON> Jenkins </PERSON> <PERSON> Norstad </PERSON>, and a daughter, <PERSON> Kristin </PERSON> <PERSON> Jaffe </PERSON>, of <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION>. A memorial service will be held Friday at the <ORGANIZATION> Davis-Monthan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Force </ORGANIZATION> Base Chapel. Burial will be Sept. 21 at <ORGANIZATION> Arlington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cemetery </ORGANIZATION>.
