 Elsewhere in television: RINTY, THE COMPLICATED ANTI-HERO? _ The <ORGANIZATION> CBN </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Family </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Channel </ORGANIZATION> announces it is launching a `` contemporary and sophisticated'' new version of the 1950s series `` Rin-Tin-Tin.'' In `` Rin-Tin-Tin K-9 Cop,'' Rinty is a member of the canine corps of a big-city police department. In the old series, he was a cavalry mascot. The half-hour drama will premiere on the cable channel Sept. 17. For those who like their dog dramas unsophisticated, <ORGANIZATION> CBN </ORGANIZATION> also airs the original `` Rin-Tin-Tin'' on Saturdays.
