<TEXT>
 The stock market opened lower in moderate trading today, as participants continued to await Wednesday's government report on the nation's trade deficit for July The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was down 10.31 points at 2,062.06. Declining issues outnumbered advances by 3-to-1, with 628 issues down, 258 up and 457 unchanged. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 25.37 million shares. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks was down 0.55 at 150.08. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index had slipped 0.64 to 296.03. On Monday, the <ORGANIZATION> Dow </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Jones </ORGANIZATION> industrial average edged up 3.56 points to 2,072.37 in a listless session. But declining issues outnumbered advances by nearly 4 to 3 on the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>, with 605 up, 789 down and 525 unchanged. <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> volume totaled 114.88 million shares, compared with 141.54 million in the previous session.
