<HEAD>Monsanto Suffers Another Setback In Copperr-7 Case</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PAUL, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A federal judge has ruled that <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> also could be held liable for damages from the Copper-7 intrauterine device that is produced by its subsidiary <ORGANIZATION> G.D. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Searle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Co. The ruling Monday by <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Judge </ORGANIZATION> <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Renner </PERSON> represents a second legal setback for <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> involving the Copper-7 device, which was taken off the market in 1986, a year after <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> acquired <PERSON> Searle </PERSON>. Last week <PERSON> Searle </PERSON> was ordered by a jury to pay $ 8.75 million in punitive and compensatory damages to <PERSON> Esther </PERSON> <PERSON> Kociemba </PERSON>, an <LOCATION> Elk </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Minn. </LOCATION>, woman who said the IUD caused her to become sterile. In the latest case, <PERSON> Renner </PERSON> ruled that <PERSON> Julie </PERSON> <PERSON> Daher </PERSON>, of <LOCATION> Columbia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Heights </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Minn. </LOCATION>, could sue both <PERSON> Searle </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> for damages from a Copper-7 she used between October 1984 and October 1987. <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Mo. </LOCATION>, had been named as co-defendant in about two dozen Copper-7 cases, but all of those cases had been dismissed in court or dropped by the plaintiffs until Monday's decision. <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> stock plunged after the ruling Monday, falling $ 7.12 -LCB- to $ 78.62 -LCB- in active trading on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. In early trading today it was off another $ 1.50 to $ 77.12 -LCB-. <PERSON> Daher </PERSON>'s attorneys claim <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> acted in concert with <PERSON> Searle </PERSON> in misrepresenting the safety of the Copper-7 and fraudulently concealing dangers associated with the device after it acquired <PERSON> Searle </PERSON> in October 1985 for $ 2.8 billion. Legal experts have said Friday's jury verdict could result in thousands of lawsuits against <PERSON> Searle </PERSON>. <ORGANIZATION> Monsanto </ORGANIZATION> maintains `` there simply is no justification for the jury's action.''
