<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices moved higher Tuesday as the market was buoyed by developments in the oil sector. Confidence was given a much needed boost by <ORGANIZATION> British </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Gas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, which staged a `` dawn raid,'' scooping up shares in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Scottish </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Marine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, known as <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION>. The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index closed up 11.7 points, or 0.7 percent, at 1,756.3. Trading volume was 369.2 million shares, compared with 213.2 million shares traded during Monday's session. Although British Gas failed to achieve its target of aquiring a 14.9-percent stake in <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION>, the hectic buying and the general speculation surrounding the raid helped the whole oil sector and share prices generally. `` You can see what happens to this market when there's a little bit of good news,'' said <PERSON> Roger </PERSON> <PERSON> Charlesworth </PERSON>, senior dealer at <ORGANIZATION> Chase </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Manhattan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. The market has lately been plagued by confusion over the near-term direction for equities and by particularly low levels of participation. The raid on <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION> started before the official market opening, with the brokerage <ORGANIZATION> Hoare </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Govett </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Ltd. </ORGANIZATION> offering to purchase <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION> shares on behalf of British Gas at 480 pence, or $ 8.16, apiece, well above Monday's closing <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION> price of 390 pence. <PERSON> Hoare </PERSON> <PERSON> Govett </PERSON> said it obtained a small amount of <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION>'s stock. The raid sparked speculation of a forthcoming takeover bid for <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION>. Takeover speculation also surrounded <ORGANIZATION> Enterprise </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION>, another independent British oil company, because of <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION>'s 25 percent holding in Enterprise. A successful bidder for <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION> could use the Enterprise holding as a platform for a bid for Enterprise as well, analysts said. <ORGANIZATION> Lasmo </ORGANIZATION> shares surged to close at 543 pence, a jump of 153 pence. Enterprise closed 126 pence higher at 562 pence.
