<HEAD>Colgate-Palmolive Subsidiary To Be Sold To Managment Group</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Consumer-products giant <ORGANIZATION> Colgate-Palmolive </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday it accepted a management-led buyout of its <ORGANIZATION> Kendall </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Care </ORGANIZATION> subsidiary in a deal that values the business at around $ 1.1 billion. Under the agreement, <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION> will receive $ 910 million in cash and $ 50 million worth of debentures from a company formed by <PERSON> Kendall </PERSON> management and the investment banking firm <ORGANIZATION> Clayton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Dublier </PERSON>. In addition, <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION> said it would retain certain <PERSON> Kendall </PERSON> assets, including real estate and some overseas non-health care consumer products businesses. It estimated the entire deal to be worth around $ 1.1 billion, a price that was in line with expectations of private industry analysts. <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION>, which put <PERSON> Kendall </PERSON> on the auction block last spring, said the transaction would result in an after-tax gain of more than $ 200 million. <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION> Chaiman <PERSON> Reuben </PERSON> <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> said the <PERSON> Kendall </PERSON> sale would enable the company to focus on its vast array of global consumer products. `` It -LRB- <PERSON> Kendall </PERSON> -RRB- is a fine, well-managed company, but as the business does not fit in with <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION>'s long-term strategic focus, the sale will enable us to concentrate all of our attention on worldwide consumer products opportunities,'' <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> said. Among <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION>'s products are Fresh Start, Fab, <ORGANIZATION> Dynamo </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Ajax </ORGANIZATION> cleansers; <ORGANIZATION> Colgate </ORGANIZATION> and <O