on that the cease-fire in the Iran-Iraq war could bring even higher production, has helped depress prices below <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION>'s benchmark of $ 18 a barrel. In addition to <LOCATION> Ecuador </LOCATION>, the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Arab </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Emirates </LOCATION> is seeking a higher quota. The U.A.E. has refused to accept a quota of 948,000 barrels a day and demanded a 1.5 million-barrel quota, roughly the level of its current production.
